#. <section class="sutta" id="sn21.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn21.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga"
msgstr "1. Monks"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn21.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Tissasutta"
msgstr "9. With Tissa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.282"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.9:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn21.9:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi dukkhī dummano assūni "
"pavattayamāno. Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Tissa—the Buddha’s cousin on his father’s side—went to the "
"Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. He was miserable and sad, with "
"tears flowing. Then the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn21.9:1.3"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho tvaṃ, tissa, ekamantaṃ nisinno dukkhī dummano assūni "
"pavattayamāno”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Tissa, why are you sitting there so miserable and sad, with tears flowing?”"

#. VAR: vācāyasannitodakena → vācāsannitodakena (bj)
#. VAR: sañjambharimakaṃsū”ti → sañjambhariṃ akaṃsūti (bj, s1-3) | sañjabbharimakaṃsūti (?)
msgctxt "sn21.9:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Tathā hi pana maṃ, bhante, bhikkhū samantā vācāyasannitodakena "
"sañjambharimakaṃsū”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, it’s because the mendicants on all sides provoke me with barbed words.”"

# BB gives the commentarial explanation, without noting that it blatantly contradicts the sutta.
msgctxt "sn21.9:1.5"
msgid "“Tathāhi pana tvaṃ, tissa, vattā no ca vacanakkhamo;"
msgstr ""
"“That’s because you admonish others, but don’t accept admonition yourself."

msgctxt "sn21.9:1.6"
msgid ""
"na kho te taṃ, tissa, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ vattā no ca vacanakkhamo."
msgstr ""
"As a son of a good family who has gone forth in faith from the lay life to "
"homelessness, it’s not appropriate for you to admonish others without "
"accepting admonition yourself."

msgctxt "sn21.9:1.7"
msgid ""
"Etaṃ kho te, tissa, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajitassa:"
msgstr "It’s appropriate for you to"

msgctxt "sn21.9:1.8"
msgid "‘yaṃ tvaṃ vattā ca assa vacanakkhamo cā’”ti."
msgstr "admonish others and accept admonition yourself.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.9:2.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn21.9:2.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.9:3.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kujjhasi mā kujjhi,"
msgstr "“Why are you angry? Don’t be angry!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.9:3.2"
msgid "Akkodho tissa te varaṃ;"
msgstr "It’s better to not be angry, Tissa."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.9:3.3"
msgid "Kodhamānamakkhavinayatthañhi,"
msgstr "For this spiritual life is lived"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.9:3.4"
msgid "Tissa brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti."
msgstr "in order to remove anger, conceit, and denigration.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.9:3.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
